sentence: James Carl Inkanish, Jr. (February 1, 1938 – November 1, 2008), known professionally as Jimmy Carl Black, was a drummer and vocalist for The Mothers of Invention.
His trademark line was "Hi Boys and Girls, I'm Jimmy Carl Black, and I'm the Indian of the group."

Black was also addressed as such by Theodore Bikel in the film 200 Motels.
